description.et:
Homework on contract law: solving cases by applying the CISG in accordance with the instructions provided by the lecturer.
Each case gives either 3 or 6 points, depending on the complexity of the case, in total max 30 points.

Assessment criteria and relevance in determination of the final score:
- Correctness of formalisation and structure of the answer (1/6);
- Use of and reference to the correct legal provisions (1/6);
- Correctness of the final answer (1/6);
- Sufficiency of explanation of the answer, level of legal analysis and establishing connections, correctness of interpretation of the relevant provisions (3/6). 
In the event that the criterion is achieved partially, 0,5 points can be given.

Test with open materials: multiple-choice questions, short answer questions, 1-2 essay questions.  
Gives max 40 points in total:
- Multiple-choice questions - 12 points;
- Short answer questions - 12 points;
- Essay questions - 16 points.

grade_preconditions.et:
1) Participation in the last seminar and at least 50% of the lectures;
2) Submission of all homeworks by the deadline; and
3) Completion of the online test in time.

grade_evaluation.et:
1)	Submission of 2 homeworks - 60% of the result;
2)	Online test on all topics of the course (on Moodle) - 40% of the result.

A student passes the course when she/he:
- has attended at least 50% of the lectures;
- has participated in the last seminar;
- has received at least 50 points in total for the assignments (2 homeworks and 1 online test), including at least 15 points for each separate assignment.

A student can receive up to 10 extra points for active participation in the lectures and seminars. These points are awarded at the discretion of the lecturers.

In case a student needs a grade for the course (in particular, foreign students), the grade will be determined in the following manner:
A = 91-100 points;
B = 81-90 points;
C = 71-80 points;
D = 61-70 points;
E = 51-60 points;
F = below 50 points.
